					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13385233#post-4838661</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13385233/scp-5460#post-4838661</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 07 Dec 2020 11:40:50 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Gaffsey</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6590029</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It's a good idea, and it's nice to see <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/the-analog-kid/">Myra Rider</a> again, but something isn't landing for me.</p> <p>My main issue is that the object itself feels largely superfluous to the article; MacKenzie could've been working on a marinade that leaves chicken crispy yet anomalously juicy, and the results would've been the same. If the object itself had been less interesting, I probably wouldn't have minded, but it feels like a bit of a waste to have &quot;you can do telepathy&quot; be reduced to a MacGuffin.</p> <p>Gonna novote.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
